==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncouple
<hw>Un*cou"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>couple</ets>.]</ety> <def>To loose, as dogs, from
their couples; also, to set loose; to disconnect; to disjoin; <as>as, to
<ex>uncouple</ex> railroad cars</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncouple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncouple
<hw>Un*cou"ple</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To roam at liberty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncourtliness</ent>⟦br⟧
